HEADWORD: Lemuria
<hw>Le*mu"ri*a</hw> <pr>(l⟦esl⟧*m⟦umac⟧"r⟦icr⟧*⟦adot⟧)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[So named from the supposition that it was the
original home of the <ets>lemurs</ets>.]</ety> <def>A hypothetical land,
or continent, supposed by some to have existed formerly in the Indian
Ocean, of which Madagascar is a remnant.</def>
<rj><au>Herschel.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lemurid</ent>⟦br⟧
